#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.130"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.130:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.130:0.2"
msgid "13. Kusināravagga"
msgstr "13. Kusināra"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.130:0.3"
msgid "130. Dutiyaanuruddhasutta"
msgstr "130. Anuruddha (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.282"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.130:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Anuruddha went up to Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged "
"greetings with him."

msgctxt "an3.130:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā anuruddho āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

msgctxt "an3.130:1.3"
msgid ""
"“idhāhaṃ, āvuso sāriputta, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena "
"sahassaṃ lokaṃ olokemi."
msgstr ""
"“Here’s the thing, Reverend Sāriputta. With clairvoyance that is purified "
"and surpasses the human, I survey the entire galaxy."

#. VAR: asammuṭṭhā → apammuṭṭhā (bj) | appamuṭṭhā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.130:1.4"
msgid ""
"Āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho "
"kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ."
msgstr ""
"My energy is roused up and unflagging, my mindfulness is established and "
"lucid, my body is tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind is immersed in "
"samādhi."

#. VAR: nānupādāya → na anupādāya (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.130:1.5"
msgid "Atha ca pana me nānupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccatī”ti."
msgstr "But my mind is not freed from the defilements by not grasping.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.130:2.1"
msgid "“Yaṃ kho te, āvuso anuruddha, evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“Well, Reverend Anuruddha, when you say:"

msgctxt "an3.130:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena sahassaṃ lokaṃ "
"volokemī’ti, idaṃ te mānasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘With clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human, I survey the "
"entire galaxy,’ that’s your conceit."

msgctxt "an3.130:2.3"
msgid "Yampi te, āvuso anuruddha, evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And when you say:"

msgctxt "an3.130:2.4"
msgid ""
"‘āraddhaṃ kho pana me vīriyaṃ asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, "
"passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggan’ti, idaṃ te uddhaccasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘My energy is roused up and unflagging, my mindfulness is established and "
"lucid, my body is tranquil and undisturbed, and my mind is immersed in "
"samādhi,’ that’s your restlessness."

msgctxt "an3.130:2.5"
msgid "Yampi te, āvuso anuruddha, evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And when you say:"

msgctxt "an3.130:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘atha ca pana me nānupādāya āsavehi cittaṃ vimuccatī’ti, idaṃ te "
"kukkuccasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘But my mind is not freed from the defilements by not grasping,’ that’s your "
"remorse."

msgctxt "an3.130:2.7"
msgid ""
"Sādhu vatāyasmā anuruddho ime tayo dhamme pahāya, ime tayo dhamme "
"amanasikaritvā amatāya dhātuyā cittaṃ upasaṃharatū”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’d be good to give up these three things. Instead of focusing on them, "
"apply your mind to the deathless.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: upasaṃhari → upasaṃhāsi (s1-3, km, pts1) | upasaṃharati (mr)
msgctxt "an3.130:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho aparena samayena ime tayo dhamme pahāya, ime tayo "
"dhamme amanasikaritvā amatāya dhātuyā cittaṃ upasaṃhari."
msgstr ""
"After some time Anuruddha gave up these three things. Instead of focusing on "
"them, he applied his mind to the deathless."

msgctxt "an3.130:3.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto "
"nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, "
"tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā "
"sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then Anuruddha, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon "
"realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual path in this very life. He "
"lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which people from "
"good families rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "an3.130:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "an3.130:3.4"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā anuruddho arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Anuruddha became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.130:3.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
